Some useful gdb commands:

To attach: gdb -p pid(this command will stop the process execution. To resume, use 'continue').
2. To get info of threads: info threads
3. To go to particular thread's frame: t tid
4. To get backtrace: bt or bt f
5. To set breakpoint: b funcName
6. To set catchpoint: catch syscall funcName
7. To view the list of breakpoints/catchpoints: info breakpoints or i b
8. To delete a breakpoint: d breakpointId
9. To set a condition on breakpoint/catchpoint: condition breakpointId condition
10. To set the condition that breakpoint/catchpoint should be triggered in a particular thread ID only:
condition breakpointId $_thread==tid
